article.headline: Houston 78, Central Florida 71
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Lanny Smith led Houston with 25 points in the team's 78-71 victory over Central Florida Wednesday. Houston (17-6, 7-3) made 12 three-pointers, holding Central Florida (10-12, 4-5) to four three-pointers. Following Smith's lead, Oliver Lafayette scored 15 points, Jahmar Thorpe scored 12 and Ramon Dyer scored 11. For Central Florida, Josh Peppers scored 17 points, Jermaine Taylor scored 16, Anthony Williams scored 15 and Dave Noel score 10. While Houston led at halftime 37-29, Central Florida actually outscored Houston in the second half 42-41 but couldn't overcome the earlier deficit.
